      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
        If your text scores poorly, knowing <strong>how to increase readability score</strong> metrics can drastically improve your content quality. The most effective strategy is to shorten long, winding sentences. Sentences containing multiple clauses are difficult to follow; splitting them into two separate thoughts immediately boosts clarity. Additionally, swap out complex, multi-syllable terms for simpler alternatives. For example, instead of writing "utilize," choose "use." Limiting passive voice construction and avoiding unnecessary adverbs are other critical techniques to adopt when learning <strong>how to improve readability score</strong> levels.
